    <section class="py-3">
      <h3>Hot Lemon Coffee</h3>
      <ol class="m-0">
        <li>
          Brew a cup of your favorite coffee (black works best).
        </li>
        <li>
          Add 1-2 teaspoons of freshly squeezed lemon juice to the coffee. Stir well.
        </li>
        <li>
          Taste the mixture. If the flavor is too tangy or bitter, add sugar or a sweetener to balance it.
        </li>
        <li>
          Garnish with a lemon slice if desired, and enjoy!
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>
    
    <section class="py-3">
      <h3>Iced Lemon Coffee</h3>
      <ol class="m-0">
        <li>
          Brew a strong cup of coffee and let it cool.
        </li>
        <li>
          Fill a glass with ice cubes.
        </li>
        <li>
          Pour the cooled coffee over the ice.
        </li>
        <li>
          Add 1-2 teaspoons of freshly squeezed lemon juice.
        </li>
        <li>
          Sweeten to taste if needed and stir well.
        </li>
        <li>
          Garnish with a lemon slice or zest for a decorative touch, and serve!
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>